  <p>American Sign Language (ASL) is a visual language. ASL is used mainly in the United States and in many parts of Canada. The shape, placement, movement of the hands,as well as facial expressions and body movements, all play important parts in conveying information.

Sign language is not a universal language — each country has its own sign language, much like spoken languages. ASL is a language with its own unique rules of grammar and syntax, and continues to grow and change over time. We hope you'll enjoy using this app to assist you in communicating with other ASL speakers and participate in ASL community events near you.</p>
